16/11/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Negotiations with the EU on visa regime facilitation will be launched on November 30th, according to a government press release Wednesday (November 15th).
Talks on readmission agreements would then begin on December 1st.
The cabinet has decided to appoint Agnesa Rusi and Antonio Sanev as heads of Macedonia's teams for the respective negotiations.
Foreign and Interior Ministers Antonio Milososki and Gordana Jankulovska also are expected to attend the opening round of talks.
Also Wednesday, parliament approved the Law on Monitoring Communications.
It had sparked wide public debate over conditions and processes for monitoring communications and the methods and rules for keeping and using the information obtained.
(Vecer - 16/11/06;
MIA, A1 TV - 15/11/06)
